

Collapsing complex ruby array 


Short one, but usefull. If you ever need to collapse complex array like this one

~~~ruby
a = ['a','b',['c','d'], e]
~~~

to

~~~ruby
  ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e']
~~~

use  *flatten*

~~~ruby
 new_array = a.flatten
~~~

http://www.ruby-doc.org/core-1.9.3/Array.html
